{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":253,"text":"B.J. was one of many fellow inmates"},{"time":3123,"text":"who had big plans for the future."},{"time":5408,"text":"He had a vision. When he got out,"},{"time":7639,"text":"he was going to leave the dope game for good and fly straight,"},{"time":10494,"text":"and he was actually working on merging his two passions into one vision."},{"time":15621,"text":"He'd spent 10,000 dollars"},{"time":17135,"text":"to buy a website that exclusively featured women"},{"time":20419,"text":"having sex on top of or inside of luxury sports cars. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26308,"text":"It was my first week in federal prison,"},{"time":29294,"text":"and I was learning quickly that it wasn't what you see on TV."},{"time":33111,"text":"In fact, it was teeming with smart, ambitious men"},{"time":37014,"text":"whose business instincts were in many cases"},{"time":39755,"text":"as sharp as those of the CEOs"},{"time":42157,"text":"who had wined and dined me six months earlier"},{"time":43986,"text":"when I was a rising star in the Missouri Senate."},{"time":48538,"text":"Now, 95 percent of the guys that I was locked up with"},{"time":51379,"text":"had been drug dealers on the outside,"},{"time":54119,"text":"but when they talked about what they did,"},{"time":57527,"text":"they talked about it in a different jargon,"},{"time":60230,"text":"but the business concepts that they talked about"},{"time":62014,"text":"weren't unlike those that you'd learn in a first year MBA class at Wharton:"},{"time":65694,"text":"promotional incentives, you never charge a first-time user,"},{"time":70198,"text":"focus-grouping new product launches,"},{"time":73769,"text":"territorial expansion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76006,"text":"But they didn't spend a lot of time reliving the glory days."},{"time":79277,"text":"For the most part, everyone was just trying to survive."},{"time":82126,"text":"It's a lot harder than you might think."},{"time":84323,"text":"Contrary to what most people think,"},{"time":87110,"text":"people don't pay, taxpayers don't pay, for your life"},{"time":90488,"text":"when you're in prison. You've got to pay for your own life."},{"time":92278,"text":"You've got to pay for your soap, your deodorant,"},{"time":95030,"text":"toothbrush, toothpaste, all of it."},{"time":97328,"text":"And it's hard for a couple of reasons."},{"time":98680,"text":"First, everything's marked up 30 to 50 percent"},{"time":101075,"text":"from what you'd pay on the street,"},{"time":102442,"text":"and second, you don't make a lot of money."},{"time":105024,"text":"I unloaded trucks. That was my full-time job,"},{"time":107293,"text":"unloading trucks at a food warehouse,"},{"time":109582,"text":"for $5.25, not an hour, but per month."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113935,"text":"So how do you survive?"},{"time":116093,"text":"Well, you learn to hustle, all kinds of hustles."},{"time":119612,"text":"There's legal hustles."},{"time":121211,"text":"You pay everything in stamps. Those are the currency."},{"time":123379,"text":"You charge another inmate to clean his cell."},{"time":125795,"text":"There's sort of illegal hustles, like you run a barbershop out of your cell."},{"time":130698,"text":"There's pretty illegal hustles: You run a tattoo parlor out of your own cell."},{"time":134920,"text":"And there's very illegal hustles, which you smuggle in,"},{"time":138203,"text":"you get smuggled in, drugs, pornography,"},{"time":142306,"text":"cell phones, and just as in the outer world,"},{"time":145773,"text":"there's a risk-reward tradeoff, so the riskier the enterprise,"},{"time":149276,"text":"the more profitable it can potentially be."},{"time":151140,"text":"You want a cigarette in prison? Three to five dollars."},{"time":156076,"text":"You want an old-fashioned cell phone that you flip open"},{"time":159381,"text":"and is about as big as your head? Three hundred bucks."},{"time":163027,"text":"You want a dirty magazine?"},{"time":165363,"text":"Well, it can be as much as 1,000 dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168747,"text":"So as you can probably tell, one of the defining aspects"},{"time":171853,"text":"of prison life is ingenuity."},{"time":175403,"text":"Whether it was concocting delicious meals"},{"time":177807,"text":"from stolen scraps from the warehouse,"},{"time":182006,"text":"sculpting people's hair with toenail clippers,"},{"time":185156,"text":"or constructing weights from boulders in laundry bags"},{"time":190780,"text":"tied on to tree limbs, prisoners learn how to make do with less,"},{"time":195549,"text":"and many of them want to take this ingenuity"},{"time":198220,"text":"that they've learned to the outside"},{"time":200406,"text":"and start restaurants, barber shops,"},{"time":202652,"text":"personal training businesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204997,"text":"But there's no training, nothing to prepare them for that,"},{"time":208492,"text":"no rehabilitation at all in prison,"},{"time":210787,"text":"no one to help them write a business plan,"},{"time":212988,"text":"figure out a way to translate the business concepts"},{"time":216246,"text":"they intuitively grasp into legal enterprises,"},{"time":219269,"text":"no access to the Internet, even."},{"time":221844,"text":"And then, when they come out, most states"},{"time":224428,"text":"don't even have a law prohibiting employers"},{"time":226780,"text":"from discriminating against people with a background."},{"time":230500,"text":"So none of us should be surprised"},{"time":232804,"text":"that two out of three ex-offenders re-offend"},{"time":235648,"text":"within five years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238236,"text":"Look, I lied to the Feds. I lost a year of my life from it."},{"time":243548,"text":"But when I came out, I vowed that I was going to do"},{"time":247207,"text":"whatever I could to make sure"},{"time":249033,"text":"that guys like the ones I was locked up with"},{"time":251466,"text":"didn't have to waste any more of their life than they already had."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255513,"text":"So I hope that you'll think about helping in some way."},{"time":259161,"text":"The best thing we can do is figure out ways"},{"time":261729,"text":"to nurture the entrepreneurial spirit"},{"time":264417,"text":"and the tremendous untapped potential in our prisons,"},{"time":267661,"text":"because if we don't, they're not going to learn any new skills"},{"time":270736,"text":"that's going to help them, and they'll be right back."},{"time":273285,"text":"All they'll learn on the inside is new hustles."},{"time":276161,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}